race.comment: PEACE SEEKER (11) ran a much better race second-up beaten less than 2L at Mornington. That's good form and she will be fitter again. Has an inside gate and it's hard to risk the premier stable. DON'T SAY NO MIKKI (1) just missed in a 56 at Horsham fresh and that also stacks right up. Can keep improving and maps for the run of the race. Wary of BERTRAND (2), who debuts for the McEvoy yard. Coffey's engagement suggests they mean business. Won both recent jumpouts and is sure to be fancied. GOOD ONYA CHAMP (5) has an awkward gate but will push forward. Spiked his figures placing at Moe and won't have to improve much to feature. SWEET ARMANI (9) won't be far away if the wide barrier is managed.
